## Tool Template

Use this page as the copyable starter for a custom tool entry.

## Directory Layout

\`\`\`text
content/
├── tags.json
├── list.json
└── my-tool/
    ├── meta.json
    ├── en.index.md
    ├── zh.index.md
    ├── en.installation.md
    ├── zh.installation.md
    ├── en.configuration.md
    ├── zh.configuration.md
    ├── en.data.md
    ├── zh.data.md
    ├── en.faq.md
    └── zh.faq.md
\`\`\`

## \`meta.json\`

\`\`\`json
{
  "title": { "en": "My Tool", "zh": "我的工具" },
  "description": {
    "en": "One-line summary for cards and page headers.",
    "zh": "用于卡片和页面头部的一句话说明。"
  },
  "github": "https://github.com/example/my-tool",
  "link": ["agent-browser"]
}
\`\`\`

## \`content/tags.json\`

\`\`\`json
[
  { "key": "devTools", "en": "Dev Tools", "zh": "开发工具" },
  { "key": "open-source", "en": "Open Source", "zh": "开源" }
]
\`\`\`

## \`content/list.json\` Entry

\`\`\`json
{
  "slug": "my-tool",
  "path": "my-group/my-tool",
  "tags": ["devTools", "open-source", "free", "cli", "web"]
}
\`\`\`

Use \`path\` only when the content directory should differ from the URL slug.
For example, \`slug: "zzci-chrome"\` can point to \`path: "zzci/chrome"\`.
Keep tag label definitions in \`content/tags.json\`, and reference their keys from \`content/list.json\`.

